FBIS4-35910 "drnes107_m_94004" FBIS-NES-94-107 Daily Report 7 Jun 1994 JORDAN Journalists Protest Media `Bias' in Yemen Crisis Journalists Protest Media `Bias' in Yemen Crisis JN0206180594 Amman SHIHAN in Arabic 4-10 Jun 94 p 2 JN0206180594 Amman SHIHAN Arabic BFN [Text] Some 61 Jordanian journalists and writers have sent a memorandum of protest to Information Minister Dr. Jawad al-'Anani against the Jordanian official media's coverage of Yemeni developments. The memorandum said that the coverage is biased and contradicts the Jordanian official position and role as a sponsor of the accord document. This coverage will also not help Jordan to play a role in the future as an honest broker and a friend of all Yemeni forces. The memorandum demanded that the official media stop showing bias.
